@node "req" "System Requirements"
 These are the System Requirements for DTInfo:
 
 
        - Workbench 3.0 (or higher)
        
        - The correct Datatypes for the pictures*
        


 * = You can find almost ANY datatype on Aminet.

@endnode

@node "install" "Installation"
 Simply copy the drawer to wherever you want DTInfo to be!

@endnode

@node "use" "Usage"
 Using DataType Info is easy!

Simply run the program, and drop a picture file onto it. A requester will then come up with some statistics about the picture, which are:
 
  DataType = (eg ILBM, GIF, JPEG/JFIF)
 
  Width    = (eg 320, 640, 1280)
  
  Height   = (eg 256, 512, 1024)
  
  Depth    = (eg 2, 4, 8)
   Simply click on "OK" and then you can drag some other files onto it!

The latest version (1.12) now supports CLI output. This means you can go to the shell, and simply type something like "DTInfo PPaint:Pictures/AmigaDOS-8.iff" and it output to the CLI. This can be useful for BBS systems.

@endnode

@node "bugs" "Bugs!"

 - If a pictures is 15-bit, 16-bit or 24-bit, DTInfo will still say that it's 256 colours. I don't think it's a bug, it's the way Blitz2 handles DataTypes, so it can't be sorted :(  

@endnode

